title: How has the number of ambulance staff changed over time?
analysis_commentary:
There is annual variation in the number of ambulance staff with a trough each summer followed by a rise as newly qualified staff join the workforce, reaching a peak in the winter. There has been an increase in the number of ambulance staff over the past years, from 16,987 in September 2009 to 18,825 in July 2016.

Updated November 2016
